    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>to prep, so get your slow cooker and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-goulash-with-mash-and-soured-cream/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Turn on your <strong>slow cooker</strong> to high</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-goulash-with-mash-and-soured-cream/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced beef </strong>and cook for 2-3 min until slightly browned</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-goulash-with-mash-and-soured-cream/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and cut your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into strips</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> roughly</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-goulash-with-mash-and-soured-cream/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once slightly browned, add your <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>onion wedges </strong>and<strong> ground smoked paprika </strong>to the pan and give it a good mix up</p><p>Cook for 1-2 min further</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-goulash-with-mash-and-soured-cream/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the contents of your pan to the <strong>slow cooker</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>pepper strips </strong>and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>carrot </strong>with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, your<strong> beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste </strong>and<strong> Henderson's Relish</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong>, then cover and cook on high for 4 hours \u2013 this is your <strong>beef goulash</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-goulash-with-mash-and-soured-cream/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the goulash is almost done, cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized cubes</p><p>Add the <strong>cubed potatoes</strong> to a large heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 6-10 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-goulash-with-mash-and-soured-cream/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, add a knob of\u00a0<strong>butter</strong>\u00a0and a generous pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt\u00a0</strong>and\u00a0<strong>pepper </strong>and mash until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>mash</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> beef goulash </strong>with the <strong>mash</strong> to the side and dollop over your<strong> soured cream</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
